# Email Template Standards

All email templates must include the brand logo at the top of the email container.

## Required structure

Every template must follow this layout order inside `.container`:

```html
<div class="container">
  <!-- 1. Logo strip — ALWAYS first, before the coloured header -->
  <div class="logo-strip">
    <img src="https://carahulgupta.in/cropped_logo.png" alt="CA Rahul Gupta" height="52" style="display:block;margin:0 auto;" />
  </div>

  <!-- 2. Coloured header (navy #1a3c6e or contextual colour) -->
  <div class="header">
    <h1>...</h1>
  </div>

  <!-- 3. Body -->
  <div class="body">...</div>

  <!-- 4. Footer -->
  <div class="footer">...</div>
</div>
```

## Required CSS (add to every `<style>` block, after `.container`)

```css
.logo-strip { background: #ffffff; padding: 20px 40px; text-align: center; border-bottom: 3px solid #F37920; }
.logo-strip img { height: 52px; width: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto; }
```

- Use `border-bottom: 3px solid #dc2626` instead when the header colour is red (`#7f1d1d`).
- For inline-style-only templates (no `<style>` block), replicate the logo strip using `style=` attributes directly on the divs.

## Logo asset

- File: `web-public/public/cropped_logo.png` (tracked in git)
- Public URL: `https://carahulgupta.in/cropped_logo.png`
- This file is copied as-is into `web-public/dist/` by Vite during build and deployed via rsync — do **not** reference hashed paths.
